       <span class="docSource"><span class="dType"><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ recipients copy (A recipients copy is assumed to be in the hand of the signer unless it is otherwise described.) ]">RC</abbr></span> (<span class="ref-terms">Adams Papers</span>); addressed: For The Honble. John Adams Esqr. In Philadelphia; docketed: Mason Aut 12. 1776.</span>
      </p>

     </div>
     <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA04d262n1-ptr" id="PJA04d262n1">1</a>
      
   <p>Three historians of England. For titles of their works, see <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;Papers of John Adams&lt;/i&gt;, ed. Robert J. Taylor and others, Cambridge, 1977. ]">JA, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Papers</span></span>, 2: index.</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA04d262n2-ptr" id="PJA04d262n2">2</a>
      
   <p>Francis S. Sullivan, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Historical Treatise on the Feudal Law, and the Constitution and Laws of England . . . Lectures in the University of Dublin</span>, London, 1770. For Blackstone, Wood, Coke, and Hawkins, see <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;Papers of John Adams&lt;/i&gt;, ed. Robert J. Taylor and others, Cambridge, 1977. ]">JA, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Papers</span></span>, 2: index.</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA04d262n3-ptr" id="PJA04d262n3">3</a>
      
   <p>Hazard, a game played with dice (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;The Oxford English Dictionary&lt;/i&gt;, Oxford, 1933; 12 vols. and supplement. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">OED</span></span>).</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA04d262n4-ptr" id="PJA04d262n4">4</a>
      
   <p>On 7 Aug., Pennsylvanias warship the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Hancock</span> captured the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Reward</span>, which was reported to have between 1,000 and 1,100 hhds. of sugar, 12 bales of cotton, and cannon aboard (<span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">New-England Chronicle</span>, 15 Aug.).</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA04d262n5-ptr" id="PJA04d262n5">5</a>
      
   <p>Capt. Joseph White, commander of the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Revenge</span>, listed his prizes, most of which were carrying sugar and rum (same, 8 Aug.; <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ William Bell Clark, William James Morgan (from vol. 5), and others, eds., &lt;i&gt;Naval Documents of the American Revolution&lt;/i&gt;, Washington, 1964- ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Naval Docs. Amer. Rev.</span></span>, 6:2930, 347). On Capt. John Derby, see James Warren to <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>, 20 July 1775, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-03-02-0049&amp;expandNote=PJA03d052n5#PJA03d052n5" class="document">note 5</a> (above).</p>

     </div>
     <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA04d262n6-ptr" id="PJA04d262n6">6</a>
      
   <p>This prize was the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Earl of Errol</span>, coming from Grenada, mentioned by James Warren (to <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>, 11 Aug., <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-04-02-0201&amp;expandNote=PJA04d261n2#PJA04d261n2" class="document">note 2</a>, above). The two New York privateers that captured it were the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Enterprize</span> and the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Beaver (Boston Gazette</span>, 19 Aug.; <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ William Bell Clark, William James Morgan (from vol. 5), and others, eds., &lt;i&gt;Naval Documents of the American Revolution&lt;/i&gt;, Washington, 1964- ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Naval Docs. Amer. Rev.</span></span>, 6:193, note 1).</p>

